: Abu Rawwad, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cThe Muslims would supplicate at the arrival of Ramadan: O Allah, the month of Ramadan has come. Grant it to me, secure me in it, and accept it from me. O Allah, provide me with its fasting,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":31924,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/09\/mala-sahaba-dua-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":31921,"position":1},"title":"Ma\u2019la on Ramadan: Companions supplicate for Ramadan all year round","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 9, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Rajab reported: Ma\u2019la ibn al-Fadl, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cThe companions would supplicate to Allah for six months prior that they would reach Ramadan. Then, they would supplicate to him for six months afterward to accept their deeds.\u201d Source: Lat\u0323a\u0304\u2019if al-Ma\u2019a\u0304rif 1\/138 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0631\u062c\u0628 \u0642\u0627\u0644\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37804,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/05\/20\/kab-intending-sin-after-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":31921,"position":2},"title":"Ka\u2019b on Ramadan: Whoever fasts intending to sin after Ramadan","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 20, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Rajab reported: Ka\u2019b ibn Malik, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cWhoever fasts the month of Ramadan and he says to himself that he will return to sinful disobedience when Ramadan is over, his fasting is rejected.\u201d Source: Lat\u0323a\u0304\u2019if al-Ma\u2019a\u0304rif 1\/222 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0631\u062c\u0628 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0628\u0652 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28484,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/29\/itikaf-ramadan-last-ten\/","url_meta":{"origin":31921,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: The Prophet secludes himself in the last ten nights","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 29, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would retreat to the mosque in the last ten nights of Ramadan. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 2025, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1171 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36130,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/11\/laylat-al-qadr-last-night\/","url_meta":{"origin":31921,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Seek Laylat al-Qadr on last night of Ramadan","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Mu\u2019awiyah ibn Abi Sufyan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cSeek the Night of Decree on the last night of Ramadan.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Ibn Khuzaymah 2189 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u064f\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0648\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0633\u064f\u0641\u0652\u064a\u064e\u0627\u0646 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":953,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/08\/01\/qiyam-al-layl-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":31921,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Forgiveness for night prayer in Ramadan","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 1, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, encouraged standing for night prayer in the month of Ramadan, without imposing it on them. The Prophet would say, \u201cWhoever stands in prayer during Ramadan due to faith and seeking reward, his previous sins will be forgiven.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u